ğŸ‡ºğŸ‡¸ Protocol
1.	Pull out Qubit standards from fridge and allow to warm to RT (~10 min). Mix gently by inverting each container several times.
2.	Pull out Qubit buffer (â€œ1x dsDNA BR Working Solutionâ€). Gently mix buffer by inverting several times.
3.	Calculate how much 1x buffer you will need with the following calculation:
Buffer = (# samples + 2 standards + 1 for error) Ã— 190 ÂµL
4.	Transfer buffer into an appropriate sized tube.
5.	Pull out enough Qubit tubes (clear, 0.5 mL) for your samples plus 2 standards. Leave the lids open.
6.	Pipet 198 ÂµL of buffer into each of the sample tubes. It is not necessary to change tips between tubes.
7.	Pipet 190 ÂµL of buffer into the 2 standard tubes.
8.	Pipet 10 ÂµL of standard 1 into one of the standard tubes and 10 ÂµL of standard 2 into the other. Close and label the standard tubes â€œS1â€ and â€œS2â€.
9.	Vortex the DNA samples for 3 seconds before pipetting 2 ÂµL into the sample tubes, using a separate filter tip for each. Make sure to insert the pipet tip into the buffer to ensure that all 2 ÂµL is dispensed. Close and label all sample tubes.
10.	Vortex all tubes for 5 solid seconds.
11.	Incubate all tubes for 3 minutes in a dark drawer.
12.	Turn on the Qubit device. Select â€œdsDNAâ€ â†’ â€œdsDNA Broad Rangeâ€ â†’ â€œRead Standardsâ€. Insert standard 1, close the lid, and press â€œread standardâ€. Repeat for standard 2.
13.	Insert your first sample and press â€œread tubeâ€. After reading, press â€œcalculate stock concentrationâ€ and adjust the sample volume to 2 ÂµL and the units to ng/ÂµL. Record the quantity, press â€œsave,â€ and note the decimal shift to easily calculate other stock concentrations.
14.	Repeat #13 for all of your samples.
